#week-title("Four", "The Personal Alchemical Spread & Year One Review")

=== Core Teaching

The Tarot is now sufficiently integrated to use as a genuine alchemical review
instrument. This week, the student conducts two complementary spreads: a review
of the Year One plant work, and a reading of the current state of Year Two.

The personal alchemical spread is not a prescribed layout — it emerges from the
student's own understanding of the Work's structure. This is itself the test: a
student who cannot design a spread that meaningfully maps their own Work has not
yet internalized the symbolic framework deeply enough. The act of designing the
spread forces integration.

*Minimum positions for a Year One review spread:*
1. The original seed intention (what the Tyro began with)
2. The Mercury — what rose and clarified in Year One
3. The Sulphur — what proved to be the unique characterising quality of the year
4. The Salt — what remained fixed, unmoved by the year's fire
5. The cohobation — what was genuinely reunited and elevated
6. What the Plant Stone currently is (its living state)
7. What Year Two is calling for

*Comparing to the Year One directional reading.* In Year One Month 5, the student
conducted a directional reading of their laboratory space. That reading is now
revisited: has the energetic condition of the space changed? What have the
intervening months done to the quality of attention and intention held within the
working environment?

The World card (Key 21, Tav/Saturn/Earth, path 32, Yesod to Malkuth) when it
appears at the centre or culmination of such a review is read as the approaching
completion of a significant phase — not the Stone, but its foreshadowing. The
dancer within the wreath has not escaped the world; she is its articulate,
integrated expression.

=== Topics This Week

- Designing a personal alchemical spread: principles and positions
- Conducting the Year One review spread
- Revisiting the Year One directional reading of the laboratory space
- Reading the World card at the Initiate level
- Preparation for Quarter II Gathering

#inner-work[
  *The Year One Review Spread*

  Using the full 78-card deck, lay a spread tracing your Year One Plant Stone
  work from beginning to present.

  Design the positions yourself, using the minimum structure above as a starting
  point. Record the layout with a sketch or photograph in your Tarot journal.
  Write a paragraph of interpretation for each position.

  Then reread the directional reading from Year One Month 5 (in your original
  Tarot journal). Write one paragraph: what has changed?
]

